    <item>
      <title>5.1. Introduction</title>
      <link>http://localhost:999/en/5_workshop/1_gioi_thieu/index.html</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:999/en/5_workshop/1_gioi_thieu/index.html</guid>
      <description>Introduction to VPC Endpoint A VPC endpoint is a virtual device. They are horizontally scaled, redundant, and highly available VPC components. They allow communication between your compute resources and AWS services without imposing availability risks. Compute resources running in a VPC can access Amazon S3 using Gateway endpoints. PrivateLink Interface Endpoints can be used by resources running in a VPC or on-premises data centers. Workshop Overview In this workshop, you will use two VPCs.</description>
